docs.abstract: With powerfully contemporary stagings of “Betrayal” and “Cyrano,” Jamie Lloyd has had an attention-grabbing year. That’s not what makes him hard to miss.
docs.snippet: With powerfully contemporary stagings of “Betrayal” and “Cyrano,” Jamie Lloyd has had an attention-grabbing year. That’s not what makes him hard to miss.
docs.lead_paragraph: LONDON — The director Jamie Lloyd was giving me a tour of his tattoos. Not the Pegasus on his chest or the skeleton astronaut floating on his back, though he gamely described those, but the onyx-inked adornments that cover his arms and hands, that wreathe his neck, that wrap around his shaved head.

headline.main: A Director Making His Mark in More Ways Than One

docs.abstract: “His courses built for tournaments are hard,” Tiger Woods once said, “ but there’s a good reason for everything.”
docs.snippet: “His courses built for tournaments are hard,” Tiger Woods once said, “ but there’s a good reason for everything.”
docs.lead_paragraph: Pete Dye, who designed many of America’s most famous golf courses and became known as the mad scientist of golf architecture for his imaginative and supremely challenging layouts, died on Thursday in the Dominican Republic, the site of several Dye family courses. He was 94.

headline.main: Pete Dye, ‘Picasso’ of Golf Course Design, Is Dead at 94
headline.print_headline: Pete Dye, Golf Designer Who Put 1,000 Hazards On 18 Holes, Dies at 94

docs.abstract: How the Hong Kong democracy movement feeds on the city’s distinct identity.
docs.snippet: How the Hong Kong democracy movement feeds on the city’s distinct identity.
docs.lead_paragraph: HONG KONG — “Who says I can’t sell an ice cream cone and add a gas mask on the side?” Chung Yiu-wa, the co-owner of Sogno Gelato, said. “I have a license to sell, and I can attach free gifts if I want. I’m not breaking any laws.”

headline.main: Tear-Gas Gelato, Foulmouthed Mooncakes and Other Foods Fit for a Revolution

docs.abstract: If a Ukrainian passenger plane was shot down in Iran on Wednesday, as American officials believe, it would join a long list of civilian aircraft brought down by armed forces.
docs.snippet: If a Ukrainian passenger plane was shot down in Iran on Wednesday, as American officials believe, it would join a long list of civilian aircraft brought down by armed forces.
docs.lead_paragraph: A Ukrainian airliner, a Boeing 737-800, went down in Iran on Wednesday morning, killing at least 176 people. American officials believe that the Iranians brought down the airliner by mistake, with two missiles fired from an Iranian air defense system, the SA-15.

headline.main: Civilian Planes Shot Down: A Grim History
headline.print_headline: Grim Look At Planes Shot Down

docs.abstract: Competing rulings this week were the latest flash point in a controversy ignited by a satire released before Christmas.
docs.snippet: Competing rulings this week were the latest flash point in a controversy ignited by a satire released before Christmas.
docs.lead_paragraph: RIO DE JANEIRO — The Supreme Court on Thursday allowed Netflix to continue showing a short film depicting Jesus as a gay man, reversing a lower court’s ruling that the film be taken down because it did “irreparable damage” to the nation’s Christians.

headline.main: Brazil’s Top Court Strikes Down Ban on Netflix Film Portraying Jesus as Gay

docs.abstract: Comparing the dangerous effects of three diseases with the minimal side effects of their corresponding vaccines.
docs.snippet: Comparing the dangerous effects of three diseases with the minimal side effects of their corresponding vaccines.
docs.lead_paragraph: Vaccines prevent diseases, and being unvaccinated carries a risk. Last year, the World Health Organization ranked vaccine hesitancy, a “reluctance or refusal to vaccinate despite the availability of vaccines,” among the top 10 health threats worldwide, alongside Ebola, H.I.V. and drug-resistant infections.

headline.main: You Are Unvaccinated and Got Sick. These Are Your Odds.
